---

<section class="section" id="acct-finstmt-definition">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">In plain terms</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Financial statements, plainly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      {%- for p in definition %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-finstmt-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Financial statements, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <p class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</p>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-finstmt-three">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The three statements</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What each one tells you &mdash; and what it doesn&rsquo;t.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Each statement answers a different question. Used alone, each one misleads. Read together, they tell the truth.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in statements %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ s.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-finstmt-signals">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">When real financial statements earn their keep</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">If any of these sound familiar, the answer is yes.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Most owners reach for proper monthly statements when a single P&amp;L stops answering the questions they&rsquo;re asking.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in signals %}
      <div class="buyer-card">
        <h3 class="buyer-card__opener">{{ s.opener | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="buyer-card__body">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-finstmt-delivers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What&rsquo;s included</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What financial statement preparation actually delivers.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">Included in monthly bookkeeping engagements. Stand-alone historical preparation quoted as fixed-fee project work.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for d in deliverables %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <p class="num">{{ d.num }}</p>
        <h3>{{ d.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ d.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-finstmt-scope">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Honest scope</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Management statements vs CPA engagements.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">We prepare the statements from clean books. External attestation and tax returns are a licensed CPA&rsquo;s work &mdash; the boundary, drawn plainly.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for s in scope %}
      <div class="stack-8">
        <h3>{{ s.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose">{{ s.body | safe }}</p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <div class="vs-scroll">
      <table class="vs-table">
        <caption class="sr-only">What financial statement preparation covers vs what a licensed CPA engagement covers</caption>
        <thead><tr><th scope="col">Capability</th><th scope="col" class="vs-table__us">Statement preparation</th><th scope="col">Licensed CPA engagement</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          {%- for r in boundary %}
          <tr><th scope="row">{{ r.cap | safe }}</th>
            <td class="vs-table__us">{% if r.us == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.us == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}<span class="vs-table__concede">{{ r.us | safe }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
            <td>{% if r.cpa == 'yes' %}<span class="mark-yes"></span><span class="sr-only">Yes</span>{% elif r.cpa == 'no' %}<span class="mark-no"></span><span class="sr-only">No</span>{% else %}<span class="vs-table__concede">{{ r.cpa | safe }}</span>{% endif %}</td>
          </tr>
          {%- endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-finstmt-beyond">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Beyond the statements</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reliable statements are the floor, not the ceiling.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>Producing the three statements accurately every month is the foundation. The real value starts when someone who understands them tells you what to do about what they show: where margin is leaking, why cash is tight, which segment is carrying the business, when to hire. That&rsquo;s where reporting becomes <strong>advisory</strong>.</p>
      <p>TechBrot layers <a href="/accounting/advisory/kpi-reporting/?intent=advisory">KPI reporting</a>, <a href="/accounting/advisory/cash-flow-management/?intent=advisory">cash flow management</a>, and performance reviews on top of reliable statements &mdash; up to a <a href="/accounting/advisory/fractional-cfo/?intent=fractional-cfo">fractional CFO</a> seat when the work becomes continuous. As automation handles the routine, this interpretation layer is where the real value now lives.</p>
      <p><strong>Can we rebuild statements for prior periods?</strong> Yes. If past periods have unreliable or missing statements &mdash; for a lender, board, sale, or tax filing &mdash; we rebuild them as part of a <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/cleanup-bookkeeping/">cleanup</a> or <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/catch-up-bookkeeping/">catch-up</a> engagement, quoted as fixed-fee project work. <a href="/accounting/advisory/?intent=advisory">Explore advisory &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-finstmt-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Financial statement questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="acct-finstmt-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="acct-finstmt-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="acct-finstmt-review">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Page review &amp; standards</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Reviewed by the ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>This page reflects how TechBrot prepares financial statements. It is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at TechBrot Inc., a Delaware-incorporated independent ProAdvisor firm, and reviewed for accuracy on statement-preparation methodology, reconciliation standards, and the boundary with licensed CPA engagements (audit, review, compilation). Where our approach or scope changes, this page is updated. Statements are delivered CPA-ready and coordinated with your tax professional for filing and any formal CPA engagement.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for r in reviewSpec %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ r.value | safe }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ r.label | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source">Page last reviewed: May 2026.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="acct-finstmt-related">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Related</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Related services.</h2>
    </header>
    {%- for n in related %}
    <div class="stack-8">
      <h3><a href="{{ n.href }}">{{ n.title | safe }}</a></h3>
      <p class="prose">{{ n.body | safe }}</p>
    </div>
    {%- endfor %}
  </div>
</section>
